The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 30 July is 56,428 (6,531.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 25 July, there were 2,644 new confirmed cases (306.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 18 July, there were 4,317 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 39% (1,673 fewer cases).
